    "summary": "Perry den Brok was born on the 27th of February 1973, in Emmen, the Netherlands. In 2001 he obtained his Ph.D. at the IVLOS Institute of Education (Utrecht University). The title of his dissertation  was \u2018Teaching and student outcomes\u2019 (2001). From October 1999 to May 2000, he worked as a research associate at the department of Multicultural and Multilingual Education of the Graduate School of Education, George Mason University, Fairfax (Virginia), USA. From May 2003 to July 2003, he was visiting scholar at the Science and Mathematics Education Centre (SMEC), Curtin University of Technology, Perth, Australia. Between July 2001 and December 2005, he conducted a post-doctoral study at IVLOS on teaching in multicultural classrooms and was educational consultant on projects in secondary and higher education. Between March 2007 and August 2010, Perry was associate professor at the Eindhoven School of Education (ESoE) at Eindhoven University of Technology. In September 2010 he became full professor (Educational Sciences for Science Education) at ESoE as well as director of research. Between september 2015 and september 2017, Perry was director (dean) of the Eindhoven School of Education. Per October 1 2017, Perry became professor / chair Education and Learning Sciences at Wageningen University & Research. In September 2018, he also became chair of the 4TU Centre for Engineering Education\n\nSpecialismen: teacher-student interpersonal behaviour, student perceptions of the learning environment, teaching in multicultural contexts, research methodology, structural equation modelling, multilevel analysis, quality assurance in education",
